<HEADLINE>
FT  13 DEC 94 / World Commodities Prices: Tea
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The good general demand was sustained, reports the Tea Brokers' Association.
Coloury Assams met strong competition and prices ruled fully firm to often
dearer. Plainer North Indians also sold well at generally higher levels. The
few brightest East Africans on offer tended 2 to 5 pence easier although
pd's were a good feature and prices advanced. Coloury mediums remained
unchanged but lesser mediums lost 2 to 4 pence. Ceylons were about steady.
Offshore: fairly good demand at around last levels. Quotations: best
available 160p/kg, good 135p/kg, good medium 128p/kg, medium 108p/kg, low
medium 80p/kg. The highest price realised this week was 161p/kg for a Kenya
pd.
</TEXT>
