<HEADLINE>
FT  13 DEC 94 / International Company News: US life insurer pays Dollars
300m for fund manager
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RICHARD WATERS
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Lincoln National, the US life insurance and financial services group based
in Fort Wayne, Indiana, said it was paying around Dollars 300m for Delaware
Management Holdings, which has Dollars 25bn under management. It will also
take on Dollars 209m of the company's debt.
The deal is another sign of the consolidation under way in the US investment
management industry.
With Delaware's Dollars 16bn of institutional assets and Dollars 9bn of
mutual funds, the enlarged Lincoln will have Dollars 60bn under management
in all. Delaware also manages Dollars 2.2bn of international bond and equity
assets in London.
