FT  13 DEC 94 / Management (The Growing Business): Italian investment in
Yorkshire company - In a Nutshell
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The Italians are coming to Pudsey, West Yorkshire. A new joint venture
between two of Italy's oldest families - Benetton and Bonomi - has made its
first development capital investment in the glass bottle mould manufacturer,
Johnson Radley.
The Pounds 13.5m deal, mainly funded by Charterhouse Development Capital,
will be the first move for the new venture, called 21 Invest, according to
Andrea Bonomi, who will be its managing director.
Bonomi says the two families will each invest about Pounds 10m in deals over
the next two years through 21 Invest. He says the group will try to
differentiate itself from some other private equity investors by helping
companies to grow and will not simply make financial investments.
In the case of the first deal, Johnson Radley will be able to invest in new
capacity to overcome current constraints on production. The company already
has about half the UK market and exports half its Pounds 15m turnover.
21 Invest pipped local venture capital houses to the Johnson Radley deal
after making contact through the packaging interests of Invest, the Bonomi
family investment company.
