<HEADLINE>
FT  13 DEC 94 / Iran to pay British creditors
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NICOSIA
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Iran's central bank will soon begin making overdue payments to British
creditors, Iran's official news agency Irna said yesterday. Irna quoted a
source at the central bank as saying debts of up to Dollars 30,000 (Pounds
19,000) would be repaid immediately and payments involving bigger amounts
would start in coming weeks. Iran chalked up more than Dollars 10bn in
foreign debt arrears by the start of this year after weak oil prices lowered
its income. It rescheduled Dollars 8bn of the debt in agreements with its
creditors led by Germany and Japan.
</TEXT>
