<HEADLINE>
FT  13 DEC 94 / World Trade News: SKF - Ventures and Contracts
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CHRISTOPHER BROWN-HUMES
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   STOCKHOLM
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
SKF, the leading manufacturer of roller bearings, yesterday announced plans
to build a factory in China in a joint venture with Shanghai Bearing Corp.
The Swedish group will hold 60 per cent of the new company, SKF Automotive
Bearings, and invest a total of SKr100m (Dollars 13.3m). The venture expects
to supply car makers in China. The new factory will be in Shanghai and
should be operational by mid-1995. SKF says the unit should enable its
Chinese sales to double from this year's SKr280m by the end of the decade.
</TEXT>
