FT  12 DEC 94 / International Company News: Provigo writes off CDollars 152m
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ROBERT GIBBENS
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   MONTREAL
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Provigo, one of Canada's top three food distributors, has written off
CDollars 152m (USDollars 110m) to cover the loss on the sale of its
California unit last month.
The write-off took the third quarter net loss to CDollars 139m, or CDollars
1.62 a share, compared with a loss of CDollars 74m, or 88 cents, after
special items a year earlier. Sales were little changed at CDollars 1.4bn.
Provigo is being restructured and on an operating level is staging a
turnround after several years of poor results.
For the nine months ended November 5, its loss was CDollars 113.2m, or
CDollars 1.37 a share, against CDollars 59.1m, or 79 cents, on sales little
changed at CDollars 4.2bn.
Provigo said its remaining Canadian business was profitable and was now
concentrating on improving performance.
