</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
More than two in five British travellers are still worried about visiting
Florida, despite its new anti-crime measures, according to a survey last
week.
However, the 'Florida fear' figure of 41 per cent was down from 50 per cent
a year ago, according to the survey from travel insurance company Home &amp;
Overseas.
There have been a number of attacks on tourists in Florida, including the
killing of a British holidaymaker.
