<HEADLINE>
FT  12 DEC 94 / Business Travel: BA ticket scam
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
British Airways is to tighten up ticketing procedures after a reservations
clerk allegedly worked a scam which gave him Pounds 160,000 worth of free
trips.
The clerk allegedly made fake reservations on BA's Concorde booking computer
which enabled him and a friend to qualify for the airline's frequent- flyer,
free-travel incentive scheme, Air Miles.
The tickets were not paid for or collected and were in a false name. After
the flights took off, the clerk allegedly changed details on the
reservations computer so it showed the pair had been aboard.
