FT  12 DEC 94 / Concern on ethnic employment
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
People from ethnic minorities are much more likely to be unemployed than
their white counterparts, although far higher numbers of young ethnic
minority Britons are studying full-time, says a report today by the Equal
Opportunities Commission and the Commission for Racial Equality.
The unemployment rate for ethnic minority women is 16 per cent, compared
with 6 per cent for white women. Ethnic minority men have a 20 per cent
unemployment rate compared with 11 per cent for white men.
The report found that even when members of ethnic minority groups attained
higher qualifications - above A-level or equivalent - unemployment levels
remain far higher than among white men and women.
